613
00:38:59,441 --> 00:39:00,842
(This uncle is actually kinda cute.)

614
00:39:04,256 --> 00:39:05,111
Thank you.

615
00:39:05,971 --> 00:39:07,308
I have to go, 61 bro.

616
00:39:08,402 --> 00:39:09,135
Okay.

617
00:39:10,643 --> 00:39:11,520
Bye, Madam Noi.

618
00:39:20,119 --> 00:39:22,738
Madam Noi, did you hear that?

619
00:39:23,451 --> 00:39:26,061
(I’m not full yet, hooman.)

620
00:39:37,162 --> 00:39:37,948
I’ll help.

621
00:39:41,113 --> 00:39:41,947
You can get on the bus, Pai.

622
00:39:59,310 --> 00:40:03,028
(Karan might be worried about making me uncomfortable.)

623
00:40:04,172 --> 00:40:06,351
(Am I uncomfortable?)

624
00:40:14,759 --> 00:40:19,031
(Sometimes I feel like a loser when I look at Karan)

625
00:40:21,135 --> 00:40:23,738
(but he never intends to make me feel bad.)

626
00:40:26,913 --> 00:40:29,593
(Sometimes I even feel relieved)

627
00:40:29,988 --> 00:40:32,336
(that in a world where I seem to fade into the background,)

628
00:40:38,778 --> 00:40:39,867
Do you want to pair with me?

629
00:40:42,055 --> 00:40:44,988
(Karan always sees me.)

630
00:40:50,618 --> 00:40:54,548
Today, I’m going to tell you about Achi.

631
00:41:00,811 --> 00:41:03,499
For all the time I’ve been working here,

632
00:41:03,513 --> 00:41:06,710
I believe many of you will agree with me

633
00:41:07,483 --> 00:41:09,648
that the free coffee is good quality.

634
00:41:11,640 --> 00:41:13,908
The free cookies taste so yummy.

635
00:41:16,649 --> 00:41:18,240
You may wonder what brand is the photocopier

636
00:41:18,888 --> 00:41:20,640
because it has never broken down or run out of ink

637
00:41:22,446 --> 00:41:25,508
or wonder if you’re using magic pens because they never run out of inks either.

638
00:41:26,307 --> 00:41:30,744
All of us are so used to these things that we think they just happen.

639
00:41:32,412 --> 00:41:34,845
But all these little conveniences,

640
00:41:35,723 --> 00:41:37,240
the magic of the pens,

641
00:41:37,611 --> 00:41:38,434
the staples,

642
00:41:38,818 --> 00:41:39,731
the printers,

643
00:41:40,456 --> 00:41:41,550
the delicious coffee,

644
00:41:42,082 --> 00:41:44,637
or the snacks you eat every day,

645
00:41:45,350 --> 00:41:48,834
there’s always someone behind all of them

646
00:41:49,387 --> 00:41:53,236
and we’ve never wondered who that is, right?

647
00:41:54,459 --> 00:41:57,511
The one who takes care of us in silence

648
00:41:57,877 --> 00:42:00,625
and makes it possible for us to do our best work every day

649
00:42:00,787 --> 00:42:03,028
without having to worry about odds and ends.

650
00:42:04,436 --> 00:42:08,068
The one who contributes to the smooth operation of every team every day.

651
00:42:08,985 --> 00:42:11,667
Please give Achi a round of applause

652
00:42:11,996 --> 00:42:14,436
as a thank you from all of our hearts.

653
00:42:25,658 --> 00:42:29,046
(Actually, I couldn’t help feeling good at the time)

654
00:42:29,553 --> 00:42:31,313
(because the things that everyone thanked me for)

655
00:42:34,664 --> 00:42:36,338
